OL,3,CCouncil goes ahead with stricter
OL,4,Cplanning controls for second homes
OL,6,FThe local authority says it has a huge
OL,7,Fhousing crisis and as a result, has
OL,8,Fbecome the first county in Wales to
OL,9,Fissue an Article 4 direction.
OL,11,FSupporters of the council's plans say
OL,12,Fthe policy is vital to maintain local
OL,13,Fhousing stock and to ensure young
OL,14,Fpeople are able to stay in the
OL,15,Fcommunities where they grew up. They
OL,16,Fsay people can no longer afford to
OL,17,Flive in their home towns, while many
OL,18,Fproperties go unused for much of the
OL,19,Fyear.
