OL,3,CCouncil goes ahead with stricter
OL,4,Cplanning controls for second homes
OL,6,FBut opponents would argue that this
OL,7,Fwon't be answer all the area's
OL,8,Fproblems.
OL,10,FIndependent Councillor and Gwynedd
OL,11,Fresident, John Brynmor Hughes said:
OL,12,F"Article 4 is seeing more people
OL,13,Fthink: 'Well, we're not welcome here.
OL,14,FTime to move, time to go.' It is a
OL,15,Fshame as people have been coming down
OL,16,Fhere for generations and now I'm
OL,17,Fseeing them go and it's sad."
OL,19,FLocals fear they will be driven out,
OL,20,Fleaving Abersoch with little tourism
OL,21,Fand less job prospects.
